# CODEOWNERS — plugin-harness
# Order matters: last matching pattern wins. Keep this file small and explicit.
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default: every file needs a code-owner review before merge.
*                                                           @sh-ai-x

# Workflow files are the highest-blast-radius surface (a hostile change
# can disable the LLM review gate itself). Pin an explicit owner so a
# future second maintainer can co-own code without co-owning CI.
# NOTE: workflows do not auto-trigger the LLM review when modified
# (anthropics/claude-code-action@v1 self-protection guard), so a human
# CODEOWNER review is the ONLY review this surface gets.
/.github/workflows/**                                       @sh-ai-x

# CI install scripts and the worktree-rule hooks: --force refresh on
# these dropped jinja2+jsonschema install steps in scripts/test.sh on
# PR #46, breaking the `test` job on the runner. Treat as security-
# sensitive.
/scripts/**                                                @sh-ai-x
/hooks/**                                                   @sh-ai-x
/.githooks/**                                               @sh-ai-x

# Branch-protection marker file: protect it so accidental deletion
# can't silently downgrade safety.
/.dev-kit/ci-config.json                                    @sh-ai-x